26/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- President Boris Tadic is recovering from surgery to repair his Achilles' tendon, which he tore playing basketball.
Renowned Finnish orthopaedic surgeon Sakari Orava led the team of doctors at Belgrade's military hospital Thursday (December 23rd).
Tadic's office says he is doing well and will be released on Monday.
(Tanjug, RTS, Beta, B92, AP - 23/12/10)
